1
00:00:03,296 --> 00:00:05,548
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,632 --> 00:00:08,301
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,426 --> 00:00:13,431
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,515 --> 00:00:18,603
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:31,282
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:33,201
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:33,284 --> 00:00:39,791
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,210 --> 00:00:45,755
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:45,838 --> 00:00:51,678
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,637 --> 00:00:54,931
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:55,014 --> 00:00:57,684
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:02,564
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,730 --> 00:01:07,777
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,027 --> 00:01:11,447
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,531 --> 00:01:17,370
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:26,713 --> 00:01:29,632
TACTICS

17
00:01:31,134 --> 00:01:34,554
DECEMBER 20, 11:50AM

18
00:01:46,649 --> 00:01:47,442
Hey...

19
00:01:47,692 --> 00:01:48,693
Yes?

20
00:01:48,735 --> 00:01:52,238
I'm actually here in Japan on
a secret investigation.

21
00:01:52,405 --> 00:01:55,533
If the Japanese police were to...

22
00:01:56,951 --> 00:01:58,036
I understand.

23
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:00,788
I won't tell anyone that I met you.

24
00:02:01,497 --> 00:02:02,790
Including my father...

25
00:02:03,541 --> 00:02:05,543
Please excuse me...

26
00:02:08,504 --> 00:02:10,089
<i>It's just as I thought.</i>

27
00:02:10,548 --> 00:02:13,009
<i>I also don't want the police
to know</i>

28
00:02:13,092 --> 00:02:16,346
<i>that I've come into contact
with an FBI agent.</i>

29
00:02:16,763 --> 00:02:19,682
<i>If my father ever found out,
he'd tell L.</i>

30
00:02:20,433 --> 00:02:22,602
<i>Raye doesn't suspect me at all...</i>

31
00:02:23,102 --> 00:02:25,980
<i>The police will deal with
what happened just now</i>

32
00:02:26,064 --> 00:02:28,149
<i>as a regular accident.</i>

33
00:02:42,955 --> 00:02:44,082
Welcome back.

34
00:02:44,582 --> 00:02:45,958
Good to be back.

35
00:02:48,336 --> 00:02:51,297
What's the matter?
Why the big sigh?

36
00:02:51,506 --> 00:02:52,799
Raye... What happened?

37
00:02:54,926 --> 00:02:57,261
I got mixed up in a bus jacking.

38
00:02:57,929 --> 00:02:59,180
A "bus-jacking"?

39
00:02:59,972 --> 00:03:03,893
A man who robbed a bank
two days ago tried to hijack a bus.

40
00:03:04,644 --> 00:03:06,562
Japan has become a scary place.

41
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:10,733
Does that mean you were
also riding on that bus?

42
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:12,151
Yeah.

43
00:03:12,735 --> 00:03:16,406
In the end, the suspect jumped
out of the bus and was hit by a car.

44
00:03:18,074 --> 00:03:19,909
Did the suspect die?

45
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:21,953
Yeah. Probably...

46
00:03:22,328 --> 00:03:24,247
I didn't have any time to
watch what happened.

47
00:03:24,664 --> 00:03:25,748
Raye...

48
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:29,419
Do you really think
that was an accident?

49
00:03:30,086 --> 00:03:31,170
What do you mean?

50
00:03:31,587 --> 00:03:33,131
Well, you were on that bus

51
00:03:33,214 --> 00:03:34,924
because you were investigating
someone, weren't you?

52
00:03:35,341 --> 00:03:37,593
The criminal probably died...

53
00:03:38,511 --> 00:03:39,804
Doesn't that mean...

54
00:03:39,929 --> 00:03:44,600
Hey, you were indeed once
a brilliant FBI agent.

55
00:03:45,268 --> 00:03:47,687
But now you're my fiancée.

56
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,982
You're no longer an agent.

57
00:03:53,735 --> 00:03:55,653
Don't say anything about
the Kira case.

58
00:03:55,987 --> 00:03:57,572
Don't get involved or take risks.

59
00:03:58,114 --> 00:03:59,532
That's what we agreed on

60
00:03:59,615 --> 00:04:03,703
when I brought you with me here
so we could meet your parents.

61
00:04:04,412 --> 00:04:06,164
I understand, Raye.

62
00:04:06,372 --> 00:04:07,623
It's just a force of habit.

63
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:08,875
Sorry.

64
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:12,336
No, I'm sorry.
Don't worry about it.

65
00:04:13,212 --> 00:04:14,630
Once we have a family,

66
00:04:14,714 --> 00:04:17,759
you'll be so busy that
you'll forget that you were an agent.

67
00:04:18,509 --> 00:04:20,887
You won't have time
for that habit to come out.

68
00:04:22,764 --> 00:04:28,311
Instead, help me think of something that
will make that father of yours like me more.

69
00:04:30,521 --> 00:04:31,606
Oh...

70
00:04:31,689 --> 00:04:35,818
Are you going to write down
the name of the agent now?

71
00:04:36,277 --> 00:04:39,989
No. I'm going to write his name
a week from today.

72
00:04:40,364 --> 00:04:43,910
If he dies right after I meet him,
I'll look suspicious.

73
00:04:44,243 --> 00:04:46,287
It would be better to do it

74
00:04:46,579 --> 00:04:49,791
once they've investigated
more people involved with the police.

75
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:54,879
For now, I'll use some
more inmates to toy with L.

76
00:04:56,839 --> 00:04:57,882
<i>L.</i>

77
00:04:59,091 --> 00:05:02,887
<i>There is another dying
message left by a victim.</i>

78
00:05:03,262 --> 00:05:04,555
Please send an image to me.

79
00:05:07,350 --> 00:05:08,893
Gods of Death...

80
00:05:10,228 --> 00:05:13,981
"L, do you know? Gods of Death."

81
00:05:15,566 --> 00:05:18,611
Does he want to say
that Gods of Death exist?

82
00:05:19,028 --> 00:05:20,279
Watari.

83
00:05:20,404 --> 00:05:23,866
Tell the police to keep
watch on the prison.

84
00:05:24,784 --> 00:05:27,787
There may be someone else
who will leave a message.

85
00:05:28,579 --> 00:05:29,747
<i>I understand.</i>

86
00:05:32,625 --> 00:05:34,710
DECEMBER 27, 3:00PM

87
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:41,175
There sure are a lot of humans...

88
00:05:41,634 --> 00:05:42,969
Are you going to do it here?

89
00:05:43,553 --> 00:05:44,971
I'll show you what I've learned

90
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:48,850
from all of the experiments and research
I've done in the past few days...

91
00:05:48,975 --> 00:05:50,059
"Experiments"?

92
00:05:50,268 --> 00:05:51,310
Yes.

93
00:05:51,394 --> 00:05:56,983
I've been testing different killing
methods on the criminals in this area...

94
00:05:57,650 --> 00:06:00,987
ACCIDENTAL DEATH DECEMBER 26, 8:30PM
DIES AFTER GETTING HIT BY A CAR.

95
00:06:00,987 --> 00:06:01,112
First, I write the cause of death
and the circumstances in the Death Note...

96
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:04,490
Then, when I write a name
in afterwards, it becomes true.

97
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:04,657
SHO HANEKURODA

98
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:08,494
<i>That's something even I didn't know...</i>

99
00:06:09,328 --> 00:06:10,329
He's here...

100
00:06:11,247 --> 00:06:12,373
Right on time...

101
00:06:17,753 --> 00:06:18,838
Mr. Raye Penber.

102
00:06:20,464 --> 00:06:21,507
I'll kill you if you turn around.

103
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:24,093
I am Kira.

104
00:06:27,013 --> 00:06:29,932
If you turn around or
put your hand in your pocket,

105
00:06:30,016 --> 00:06:31,475
I Will kill you.

106
00:06:32,143 --> 00:06:33,811
<i>I-It couldn't be...</i>

107
00:06:34,186 --> 00:06:36,772
<i>But this voice...
I've heard it somewhere...</i>

108
00:06:37,481 --> 00:06:40,067
I shall first prove to
you that I am Kira.

109
00:06:40,568 --> 00:06:43,404
I'll kill the man
with the glasses...

110
00:06:43,863 --> 00:06:47,450
working at the coffee shop
you are looking at.

111
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:48,993
T-That's impossible!

112
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:50,786
Don't do it!

113
00:06:56,292 --> 00:06:57,460
I had no choice.

114
00:06:57,543 --> 00:07:00,004
I thought that if I didn't kill
at least one person,

115
00:07:00,087 --> 00:07:01,505
you wouldn't believe me.

116
00:07:02,340 --> 00:07:06,302
That man has been repeatedly
accused of sexual assault,

117
00:07:06,385 --> 00:07:09,138
but the police have never convicted
him due to lack of evidence.

118
00:07:09,889 --> 00:07:12,391
He was a menace and
deserved to be punished.

119
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,978
You may already have
heard from L,

120
00:07:16,062 --> 00:07:20,024
that I cannot kill someone
unless I know his face.

121
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:25,112
I could kill everyone you see here.

122
00:07:25,613 --> 00:07:27,740
If you have any requests,
I'll do it.

123
00:07:27,949 --> 00:07:29,659
D-Don't do it.

124
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:31,827
I believe that you're Kira...

125
00:07:32,453 --> 00:07:36,082
Of course, you care more about
your loved ones more

126
00:07:36,165 --> 00:07:40,294
than the people here, don't you?

127
00:07:40,628 --> 00:07:44,173
Consider them hostages.

128
00:07:44,382 --> 00:07:46,467
Y-You know about her?!

129
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:50,221
That's right.

130
00:07:50,471 --> 00:07:52,306
I've been studying you.

131
00:07:52,682 --> 00:07:55,518
I will kill everyone,

132
00:07:55,851 --> 00:07:59,438
including your family if
you don't do exactly as I say.

133
00:07:59,730 --> 00:08:01,148
You included, of course.

134
00:08:01,649 --> 00:08:02,775
L-| understand.

135
00:08:02,858 --> 00:08:04,485
What do you want me to do?

136
00:08:04,735 --> 00:08:06,904
You have a computer
with you, don't you?

137
00:08:07,113 --> 00:08:11,283
Is there a file on the agents
who've come to Japan?

138
00:08:11,993 --> 00:08:15,496
My laptop is for work. I always
carry it around with me.

139
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:17,790
But those files aren't in it.

140
00:08:18,124 --> 00:08:19,875
Then take this envelope.

141
00:08:23,004 --> 00:08:27,466
First, take out the transceiver
and put on the earphone.

142
00:08:28,926 --> 00:08:30,344
<i>A transceiver...</i>

143
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:32,138
<i>It's almost like a toy...</i>

144
00:08:32,638 --> 00:08:36,392
<i>But this won't leave
a transmission record anywhere</i>

145
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:39,270
<i>and we can converse at
close distances even underground.</i>

146
00:08:39,437 --> 00:08:40,563
<i>He's thought this out.</i>

147
00:08:41,814 --> 00:08:44,191
<i>Please take the Yamanote Line.</i>

148
00:08:44,817 --> 00:08:47,611
<i>It doesn't matter if you take
the inner circle or outer circle.</i>

149
00:08:50,656 --> 00:08:55,036
SHIBUYA - SHINAGAWA

150
00:08:55,661 --> 00:08:57,538
<i>Even while you're on the train,
keep your eyes fon/vard...</i>

151
00:08:57,621 --> 00:08:59,123
<i>...focused on one spot.</i>

152
00:08:59,623 --> 00:09:02,126
<i>Don't forget, I can kill at any time.</i>

153
00:09:02,668 --> 00:09:06,505
<i>Once you're on the train,
sit in the corner closest t0 the door.</i>

154
00:09:06,672 --> 00:09:09,091
<i>If it's taken, wait until it's free.</i>

155
00:09:25,691 --> 00:09:27,443
<i>First, I must tell you something.</i>

156
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:30,905
<i>If your answer differs significantly
from what I expect,</i>

157
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:32,740
<i>I will kill your girlfriend.</i>

158
00:09:33,699 --> 00:09:35,534
<i>Of the FBI agents who have
come to Japan,</i>

159
00:09:35,618 --> 00:09:37,912
<i>how many are there and
how are they organized?</i>

160
00:09:37,995 --> 00:09:39,663
<i>Please answer
into the transceiver.</i>

161
00:09:40,831 --> 00:09:42,291
I've heard it's f-four teams...

162
00:09:42,374 --> 00:09:44,001
a total of twelve people...

163
00:09:44,752 --> 00:09:47,588
<i>Next, take out what's in the envelope.</i>

164
00:09:54,303 --> 00:09:56,514
<i>What. . .is this?</i>

165
00:09:56,931 --> 00:09:58,474
<i>Of those investigators...</i>

166
00:09:58,557 --> 00:10:03,479
<i>Write the name of the agent
who is directly in charge of you all...</i>

167
00:10:03,562 --> 00:10:05,898
<i>in the space at the top.</i>

168
00:10:06,774 --> 00:10:08,400
<i>What is the meaning of this?</i>

169
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:09,819
<i>What is he planning?</i>

170
00:10:10,444 --> 00:10:13,155
<i>But I have to do as he says.</i>

171
00:10:13,697 --> 00:10:16,242
<i>He shouldn't be able to kill
with just names alone...</i>

172
00:10:16,909 --> 00:10:18,828
<i>Next, open your laptop.</i>

173
00:10:19,245 --> 00:10:22,540
<i>You should be receiving
a file from your superior soon.</i>

174
00:10:22,915 --> 00:10:27,002
<i>A file of all the names and faces
of the FBI agents who came to Japan.</i>

175
00:10:27,878 --> 00:10:29,630
<i>T-This is... What's going on?</i>

176
00:10:31,257 --> 00:10:33,634
<i>Now, like you just did,</i>

177
00:10:33,717 --> 00:10:38,681
<i>take a good look at each agent's face as
you write their names on the envelope.</i>

178
00:10:40,432 --> 00:10:41,517
<i>I don't understand.</i>

179
00:10:41,976 --> 00:10:44,145
<i>What is Kira trying to do?</i>

180
00:10:44,979 --> 00:10:46,397
<i>What is he doing?</i>

181
00:10:50,943 --> 00:10:52,444
<i>It seems like you're done.</i>

182
00:10:53,028 --> 00:10:55,656
Now put the transceiver and
envelope with the names on it

183
00:10:55,781 --> 00:10:58,576
back into their original envelope
and put them on the rack.

184
00:10:59,118 --> 00:11:01,245
Now put your hands on your lap
and continue riding the train

185
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:03,247
<i>without making any movements for
about thirty minutes.</i>

186
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:05,708
<i>When you are sure that
nobody has noticed</i>

187
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:09,837
<i>that you have forgotten the envelope...
get off of the train.</i>

188
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:17,803
<i>Why? Why can't I remember
that voice?</i>

189
00:11:27,730 --> 00:11:28,981
<i>Kira...</i>

190
00:11:29,064 --> 00:11:30,524
<i>Who are you?</i>

191
00:11:49,501 --> 00:11:51,670
<i>Light... Yagami...</i>

192
00:11:53,005 --> 00:11:55,174
Farewell, Raye Penber.

193
00:12:02,723 --> 00:12:06,769
<i>Raye Penber wrote those names
on pages taken from the Death Note.</i>

194
00:12:07,478 --> 00:12:11,941
<i>He unwittingly killed
all of his colleagues.</i>

195
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:17,821
<i>Penber's superior died after sending him
the file on all of the agents.</i>

196
00:12:17,821 --> 00:12:17,863
HEART ATTACK AFTER SENDING THE FILES ON THE FBI
AGENTS VVHO CAME TC) JAPAN TC) INVESTIGATE KIRA.

197
00:12:18,781 --> 00:12:21,242
<i>The rest of the agents all died
of heart attacks</i>

198
00:12:21,325 --> 00:12:23,535
<i>after the file was received.</i>

199
00:12:38,133 --> 00:12:42,179
<i>L... We have a call
from the Director of the FBI.</i>

200
00:12:43,639 --> 00:12:44,890
It's me...

201
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:47,142
I've just got word
from Japan that

202
00:12:47,142 --> 00:12:49,478
<i>all of our agents have died.</i>

203
00:12:50,521 --> 00:12:52,690
They all died of heart attacks.

204
00:12:52,815 --> 00:12:55,192
I can only think that
Kira killed them.

205
00:12:56,068 --> 00:12:57,695
L, I'm very sorry, but...

206
00:12:58,028 --> 00:13:01,824
The FBI will call off
our investigation in Japan.

207
00:13:03,701 --> 00:13:05,536
<i>It's from Chief Yagami.</i>

208
00:13:06,453 --> 00:13:10,082
<i>L, I've just spoken with
the FBI Director.</i>

209
00:13:10,916 --> 00:13:12,376
<i>According to him,</i>

210
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:17,339
<i>you were investigating everyone here
involved with the task force.</i>

211
00:13:18,424 --> 00:13:19,508
Yes.

212
00:13:19,591 --> 00:13:20,884
<i>What is the meaning of this?</i>

213
00:13:21,427 --> 00:13:24,013
<i>Are you saying that you suspect us?</i>

214
00:13:24,722 --> 00:13:28,309
I decided that it was necessary
to learn Kira's identity.

215
00:13:28,976 --> 00:13:30,269
<i>I cannot condone this.</i>

216
00:13:30,644 --> 00:13:32,730
<i>I cannot believe
that you would spy...</i>

217
00:13:33,105 --> 00:13:35,065
on your colleagues...

218
00:13:35,774 --> 00:13:38,777
We can't trust L...

219
00:13:39,194 --> 00:13:42,281
Besides, Kira killed
those FBI agents, right?

220
00:13:42,823 --> 00:13:44,033
Even if they're not criminals,

221
00:13:44,116 --> 00:13:45,951
he'll kill anyone who
stands in his way!

222
00:13:46,535 --> 00:13:49,330
<i>Kira's really just a murderer!</i>

223
00:13:51,248 --> 00:13:53,834
<i>L. Another victim has
left a message.</i>

224
00:13:56,211 --> 00:14:00,341
L, do you know? Gods of Death...

225
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:05,846
love apples...

226
00:14:07,181 --> 00:14:08,307
<i>Damn you, Kira!</i>

227
00:14:14,271 --> 00:14:16,732
Raye's. . .dead...

228
00:14:18,025 --> 00:14:21,737
No, he was killed by Kira...

229
00:14:26,742 --> 00:14:28,994
What? A family meeting?

230
00:14:29,912 --> 00:14:32,831
Even if I kept it secret,
you'd find out sooner or later.

231
00:14:33,082 --> 00:14:34,458
So I'm going to tell you now.

232
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:40,381
I am currently in charge of
conducting the Kira investigation.

233
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:42,299
No way!

234
00:14:42,383 --> 00:14:45,052
Dad, you really are amazing.

235
00:14:45,469 --> 00:14:47,554
That isn't what I wanted to say.

236
00:14:49,973 --> 00:14:51,433
Yesterday...

237
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:58,023
twelve FBI agents,
sent to Japan to find Kira, died.

238
00:14:58,649 --> 00:15:00,401
Does that mean that
they were killed by Kira?

239
00:15:00,484 --> 00:15:01,485
What?!

240
00:15:01,693 --> 00:15:06,407
It means Kira might kill anyone
who tries to apprehend him...

241
00:15:07,658 --> 00:15:08,867
It's a cold
and ruthless crime

242
00:15:08,951 --> 00:15:10,119
more fearsome than anything
we've encountered before.

243
00:15:10,327 --> 00:15:11,995
Many of my officers have quit.

244
00:15:12,663 --> 00:15:14,498
Dad, you should quit too!

245
00:15:14,581 --> 00:15:16,792
I don't want you to die!

246
00:15:17,126 --> 00:15:20,045
She's right. You should place
your life before your job.

247
00:15:20,546 --> 00:15:24,007
No. I will not remove myself
from this case.

248
00:15:24,591 --> 00:15:26,427
I will not yield to evil.

249
00:15:27,261 --> 00:15:28,637
Dad...

250
00:15:28,804 --> 00:15:29,930
Dear...

251
00:15:31,807 --> 00:15:36,228
Dad, that's admirable.
I'm proud of you.

252
00:15:37,062 --> 00:15:39,189
If anything ever happens to you,

253
00:15:39,523 --> 00:15:42,693
I'll see that
Kira gets executed.

254
00:15:48,532 --> 00:15:50,951
Kira will probably kill all who
oppose him,

255
00:15:51,034 --> 00:15:52,703
even if they're not criminals.

256
00:15:53,579 --> 00:15:56,123
We may all be killed by Kira...

257
00:15:57,082 --> 00:16:01,211
Think of your lives,
your families, and friends.

258
00:16:02,379 --> 00:16:05,757
If anyone wants to be removed
from this investigation, please resign.

259
00:16:07,092 --> 00:16:09,136
If you resign,
you will not be demoted.

260
00:16:09,261 --> 00:16:10,345
I promise you.

261
00:16:11,763 --> 00:16:14,475
I want those with the confidence
to stay on the case to fight Kira,

262
00:16:15,017 --> 00:16:18,812
even if going after him means
sacrificing everything.

263
00:16:19,938 --> 00:16:20,981
That is all.

264
00:16:21,899 --> 00:16:23,901
Hey...
What are you going to do?

265
00:16:24,234 --> 00:16:25,235
Yeah...

266
00:16:26,153 --> 00:16:28,447
Yeah, right, that's him.

267
00:16:29,281 --> 00:16:31,200
I remember him because
he said, "Get down."

268
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:34,244
But I don't really remember
the other passengers...

269
00:16:35,329 --> 00:16:36,330
I see.

270
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:39,666
I understand.
Thank you very much.

271
00:16:43,462 --> 00:16:46,548
<i>If what I'm thinking is correct,</i>

272
00:16:46,632 --> 00:16:49,426
<i>Kira could have been
among those passengers...</i>

273
00:16:50,385 --> 00:16:54,431
<i>If that's so, I can find Kira
along the path this bus takes.</i>

274
00:16:55,098 --> 00:16:56,975
SERIAL MURDER
SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS HQ

275
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:06,985
Only five people, huh?
Six including myself.

276
00:17:07,611 --> 00:17:12,616
No, I should say as many as five
of you are willing to risk your lives.

277
00:17:13,784 --> 00:17:17,454
<i>I trust all of you who have
a strong sense of justice.</i>

278
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:20,624
W-Wait just a moment.

279
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:23,627
I says he trusts us, but...

280
00:17:24,336 --> 00:17:26,421
We don't trust L.

281
00:17:27,172 --> 00:17:31,677
L, we have decided to
risk our lives to catch Kira.

282
00:17:32,678 --> 00:17:35,806
You should know what
we mean by that.

283
00:17:36,265 --> 00:17:40,269
But you never show your face
and just order us around...

284
00:17:40,894 --> 00:17:44,147
We cannot work with
someone like that!

285
00:17:48,151 --> 00:17:49,152
L.

286
00:17:49,695 --> 00:17:54,866
If you want to work with us
and want to catch Kira...

287
00:17:55,617 --> 00:17:57,869
Would it be possible for
you to come here?

288
00:18:00,706 --> 00:18:05,002
<i>Earlier, I said that I trust you all.</i>

289
00:18:13,510 --> 00:18:16,888
PLEASE KEEP WHAT IS ABOUT TO HAPPEN
A SECRET BETWEEN THE EIGHT OF US.

290
00:18:17,014 --> 00:18:19,224
I WOULD LIKE TO MEET THE SIX OF YOU,
WHOM I TRUST AS SOON AS POSSIBLE

291
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:24,104
BEFORE THAT, I WANT YOU ALL TO GO
OUTSIDE OF THE POLICE BUILDING

292
00:18:24,229 --> 00:18:27,566
AND DECIDE ONCE MORE
IF YOU TRUST ME OR NOT.

293
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:29,818
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY AND
NATIONAL PUBLIC SAFETY COMMISSION

294
00:18:29,901 --> 00:18:32,321
Why does he suddenly
want to work with just the six of us?

295
00:18:33,155 --> 00:18:37,451
If he's solved numerous difficult
cases by himself,

296
00:18:37,826 --> 00:18:39,578
he should do the same
this time, too.

297
00:18:39,995 --> 00:18:42,789
And judging by the way that L
has been conducting the investigation,

298
00:18:42,873 --> 00:18:46,001
he'll probably send a double
to meet us.

299
00:18:46,543 --> 00:18:49,129
A double, huh? It's possible...

300
00:18:49,755 --> 00:18:52,049
I-| trust L.

301
00:18:52,674 --> 00:18:56,386
I also think we need L's help
in this case.

302
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,388
Me too...

303
00:18:59,097 --> 00:19:01,058
I said from the beginning that...

304
00:19:01,141 --> 00:19:04,811
he needed the police's help
in this case.

305
00:19:05,729 --> 00:19:07,272
Perhaps you could
think of it like this.

306
00:19:08,231 --> 00:19:10,692
I was waiting
for this to happen.

307
00:19:11,526 --> 00:19:12,903
For what to happen?

308
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:14,905
There were people
in the investigation

309
00:19:14,988 --> 00:19:17,783
who distrusted L
from the beginning.

310
00:19:18,784 --> 00:19:21,203
Then we had detectives
continuously resign...

311
00:19:21,953 --> 00:19:25,248
and confidential information
was leaked.

312
00:19:25,332 --> 00:19:27,542
You can't run an investigation
unless you trust your partners.

313
00:19:27,793 --> 00:19:29,920
In other words, L was waiting
for the task force

314
00:19:30,003 --> 00:19:33,382
to get down to the people he can trust

315
00:19:33,465 --> 00:19:35,967
and who will face evil
without fear.

316
00:19:36,551 --> 00:19:37,552
Yes.

317
00:19:39,262 --> 00:19:42,182
I'll resign rather than
join up with L.

318
00:19:43,308 --> 00:19:44,643
Don't worry.

319
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:47,688
I won't trail you and
try to find L.

320
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:54,319
I trust L and will try
to cooperate with him.

321
00:19:54,569 --> 00:19:55,612
Me too...

322
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:03,495
I <i>am currently in a room</i>
<i>at the 719/70 Hotel.</i>

323
00:20:03,954 --> 00:20:07,082
<i>I shall be switching hotels from
now on every few days.</i>

324
00:20:07,582 --> 00:20:09,626
<i>From now on, I want you to
think of these rooms as...</i>

325
00:20:09,710 --> 00:20:11,920
<i>the de facto HQ of
the investigation.</i>

326
00:20:13,004 --> 00:20:15,215
<i>If you can agree to these terms...</i>

327
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:19,761
<i>I want you t0 split into two groups,
with a 30-minute interval between you,</i>

328
00:20:19,845 --> 00:20:23,306
<i>and come here by...
twelve o'clock midnight.</i>

329
00:20:26,643 --> 00:20:33,567
<i>Kira, we're even in how far we've
closed the distance between us.</i>

330
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:35,944
<i>Fine.</i>

331
00:20:36,194 --> 00:20:40,031
<i>I'll show myself to others as L
for the first time.</i>

332
00:20:41,533 --> 00:20:47,497
<i>If you manage to find out
about this, you'll definitely move in closer.</i>

333
00:20:48,373 --> 00:20:49,583
<i>Bring it on.</i>

334
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:54,504
<i>I did a lot these past few days.</i>

335
00:20:55,547 --> 00:20:56,673
<i>Think.</i>

336
00:20:56,965 --> 00:20:58,925
<i>Was there something that I missed?</i>

337
00:20:59,009 --> 00:21:01,887
<i>And. . .what is my next move?</i>

338
00:21:04,222 --> 00:21:07,517
<i>L, the real battle starts now.</i>

339
00:21:15,108 --> 00:21:17,652
Please come in.

340
00:21:23,825 --> 00:21:26,828
TO BE CONTINUED

341
00:21:27,287 --> 00:21:32,250
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

342
00:21:32,334 --> 00:21:37,631
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

343
00:21:37,923 --> 00:21:41,176
I'm holding these feelings

344
00:21:41,259 --> 00:21:46,640
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

345
00:21:46,765 --> 00:21:53,021
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

346
00:21:53,104 --> 00:21:57,609
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

347
00:21:58,443 --> 00:22:03,323
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

348
00:22:03,532 --> 00:22:07,118
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

349
00:22:07,202 --> 00:22:10,789
<i>To accomplish</i>

350
00:22:11,373 --> 00:22:15,961
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

351
00:22:16,169 --> 00:22:21,591
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

352
00:22:21,675 --> 00:22:26,721
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

353
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:32,519
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

354
00:22:36,773 --> 00:22:38,483
PREVIEW

355
00:22:38,483 --> 00:22:42,237
if this woman had told the police
all this before she told me...

356
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:48,785
This Shinigami may not be on my side,
but it looks like another god is.

357
00:22:49,119 --> 00:22:51,830
NEXT EPISODE: UNRAVELING

